<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="55" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1437,1446,2011]" pageId="18" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1446,1471]" pageId="18" pageNumber="55">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Anterior katepisternal seta absent (Pl. 1G). First and 2nd tarsomeres of male foreleg dorsodistally extended, with sex-combs: 1 
<taxonomicName box="[471,611,1483,1507]" pageId="18" pageNumber="55" rank="subSpecies" subSpecies="tarsomere">st tarsomere</taxonomicName>
with a longitudinal row of 22–29 black, apically blunt teeth along entire length of 1 
<taxonomicName box="[269,408,1519,1543]" pageId="18" pageNumber="55" rank="subSpecies" subSpecies="tarsomere">st tarsomere</taxonomicName>
and a cluster of ca. 6 black, apically sharp teeth distally; 2nd tarsomere with a distal cluster of 3–4 black, apically sharp teeth (
<figureCitation box="[549,667,1554,1579]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="19.[151,250,1810,1832]" captionTargetBox="[150,1436,373,1789]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[150,1436,373,1789]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 9. Lordiphosa anthophilia sp. nov. (A, B: paratype 05609; C−M: holotype 05610; N−P: paratype 05606). A, sex-combs on right foreleg (ventrolateral view); B, clusters of sex-comb teeth on distal extensions of 1st and 2nd tarsomeres (ventral view); C, D, periphallic organs (caudal and caudolateral view, respectively); E, epandrial ventral lobe (lateral view); F, surstyli and ventral spines of cercus (caudal view); G, inner surface of surstylus (caudolateral view); H, 10th sternite (ventral view); I̅K, phallic organs (ventral, ventrolateral, and lateral view, respectively); L, M, apical portion of paramere(s), gonopods, and aedeagus (caudal and lateral view, respectively); N, O, oviscapt (ventral and lateral view, respectively); P, spermatheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1439539/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="55">Fig. 9A,B</figureCitation>
). Cercus ventrally truncated, with a fringe of 5–7 spines on ventral margin (
<figureCitation box="[246,358,1590,1615]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="19.[151,250,1810,1832]" captionTargetBox="[150,1436,373,1789]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[150,1436,373,1789]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 9. Lordiphosa anthophilia sp. nov. (A, B: paratype 05609; C−M: holotype 05610; N−P: paratype 05606). A, sex-combs on right foreleg (ventrolateral view); B, clusters of sex-comb teeth on distal extensions of 1st and 2nd tarsomeres (ventral view); C, D, periphallic organs (caudal and caudolateral view, respectively); E, epandrial ventral lobe (lateral view); F, surstyli and ventral spines of cercus (caudal view); G, inner surface of surstylus (caudolateral view); H, 10th sternite (ventral view); I̅K, phallic organs (ventral, ventrolateral, and lateral view, respectively); L, M, apical portion of paramere(s), gonopods, and aedeagus (caudal and lateral view, respectively); N, O, oviscapt (ventral and lateral view, respectively); P, spermatheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1439539/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="55">Fig. 9C,F</figureCitation>
). Parameres as long as aedeagus, apically curved ventrad and inward, sometimes cruciate, with several minute warts and sensilla scattered on apical to subapical surface (
<figureCitation box="[1008,1141,1626,1651]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="19.[151,250,1810,1832]" captionTargetBox="[150,1436,373,1789]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[150,1436,373,1789]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 9. Lordiphosa anthophilia sp. nov. (A, B: paratype 05609; C−M: holotype 05610; N−P: paratype 05606). A, sex-combs on right foreleg (ventrolateral view); B, clusters of sex-comb teeth on distal extensions of 1st and 2nd tarsomeres (ventral view); C, D, periphallic organs (caudal and caudolateral view, respectively); E, epandrial ventral lobe (lateral view); F, surstyli and ventral spines of cercus (caudal view); G, inner surface of surstylus (caudolateral view); H, 10th sternite (ventral view); I̅K, phallic organs (ventral, ventrolateral, and lateral view, respectively); L, M, apical portion of paramere(s), gonopods, and aedeagus (caudal and lateral view, respectively); N, O, oviscapt (ventral and lateral view, respectively); P, spermatheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1439539/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="55">Fig. 9K–M</figureCitation>
). Aedeagus long, apically strongly curved ventrad and bearing thick hairs like “mop of hair” (
<figureCitation box="[929,1062,1662,1687]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="19.[151,250,1810,1832]" captionTargetBox="[150,1436,373,1789]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[150,1436,373,1789]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 9. Lordiphosa anthophilia sp. nov. (A, B: paratype 05609; C−M: holotype 05610; N−P: paratype 05606). A, sex-combs on right foreleg (ventrolateral view); B, clusters of sex-comb teeth on distal extensions of 1st and 2nd tarsomeres (ventral view); C, D, periphallic organs (caudal and caudolateral view, respectively); E, epandrial ventral lobe (lateral view); F, surstyli and ventral spines of cercus (caudal view); G, inner surface of surstylus (caudolateral view); H, 10th sternite (ventral view); I̅K, phallic organs (ventral, ventrolateral, and lateral view, respectively); L, M, apical portion of paramere(s), gonopods, and aedeagus (caudal and lateral view, respectively); N, O, oviscapt (ventral and lateral view, respectively); P, spermatheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1439539/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="55">Fig. 9K–M</figureCitation>
). Spermathecal capsule wrinkled horizontally in basal 1/4 or less, without apical indentation (
<figureCitation box="[823,909,1698,1723]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="19.[151,250,1810,1832]" captionTargetBox="[150,1436,373,1789]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[150,1436,373,1789]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 9. Lordiphosa anthophilia sp. nov. (A, B: paratype 05609; C−M: holotype 05610; N−P: paratype 05606). A, sex-combs on right foreleg (ventrolateral view); B, clusters of sex-comb teeth on distal extensions of 1st and 2nd tarsomeres (ventral view); C, D, periphallic organs (caudal and caudolateral view, respectively); E, epandrial ventral lobe (lateral view); F, surstyli and ventral spines of cercus (caudal view); G, inner surface of surstylus (caudolateral view); H, 10th sternite (ventral view); I̅K, phallic organs (ventral, ventrolateral, and lateral view, respectively); L, M, apical portion of paramere(s), gonopods, and aedeagus (caudal and lateral view, respectively); N, O, oviscapt (ventral and lateral view, respectively); P, spermatheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1439539/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="55">Fig. 9P</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="20" lastPageNumber="57" pageId="18" pageNumber="55" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1437,1446,2011]" pageId="18" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,338,1734,1759]" pageId="18" pageNumber="55">Description</emphasis>
(characters commonly seen in 
<taxonomicName authority="Katoh &amp; Zhang &amp; Toda &amp; Zhang &amp; Gao, 2018" authorityName="Katoh &amp; Zhang &amp; Toda &amp; Zhang &amp; Gao" authorityYear="2018" box="[699,838,1734,1758]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Lordiphosa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mikioides" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[699,714,1735,1758]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="55">L</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[731,838,1734,1758]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="55">mikioides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[847,939,1734,1759]" pageId="18" pageNumber="55" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[847,939,1734,1759]" pageId="18" pageNumber="55">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
not repeated) (
<specimenCount box="[1117,1140,1735,1759]" pageId="18" pageNumber="55" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
, 
<specimenCount box="[1154,1174,1735,1759]" pageId="18" pageNumber="55" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
). Head (Pls 1G, 3–5G, 7G): Frontal vitta orange brown. Fronto-orbital pale grayish brown. Ocellar triangle dark brown. Gena pale yellow. Antennal pedicel pale yellow; 1 
<taxonomicName box="[507,678,1806,1831]" pageId="18" pageNumber="55" rank="subSpecies" subSpecies="flagellomere">st flagellomere</taxonomicName>
yellowish white; arista with 3–4 dorsal and 1 ventral branches and small terminal bifurcation. Supracervical setulae 18¯21 per side; postocular setae 23–25 per side. Clypeus pale yellow. Cibarium with 18–22 medial and 13–15 posterior sensilla per side. Prementum whitish yellow, with 5–6 (1–2 proximal, 2 lateral, and 2 distal) pairs of setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1437,1446,2011]" lastBlockId="19.[151,1437,151,320]" lastPageId="19" lastPageNumber="56" pageId="18" pageNumber="55">Thorax (Pl. 1G): Postpronotal lobe pale grayish brown, dark brown on anterior margin. Mesonotum yellowish brown, with 3 dark brown, longitudinal stripes; medial stripe anteriorly indistinct, caudally broadened; outer stripes interrupted at transverse suture, sometimes very indistinct. Scutellum yellowish brown, laterally brown. Notopleuron pale grayish brown. Thoracic pleura pale yellow to whitish yellow. Acrostichal setulae in ca. 6 irregular rows. Mid katepisternal seta indistinguishable from those below it.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1437,151,320]" pageId="19" pageNumber="56">
Legs (Pl. 1G, 
<figureCitation box="[356,473,260,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="19.[151,250,1810,1832]" captionTargetBox="[150,1436,373,1789]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[150,1436,373,1789]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 9. Lordiphosa anthophilia sp. nov. (A, B: paratype 05609; C−M: holotype 05610; N−P: paratype 05606). A, sex-combs on right foreleg (ventrolateral view); B, clusters of sex-comb teeth on distal extensions of 1st and 2nd tarsomeres (ventral view); C, D, periphallic organs (caudal and caudolateral view, respectively); E, epandrial ventral lobe (lateral view); F, surstyli and ventral spines of cercus (caudal view); G, inner surface of surstylus (caudolateral view); H, 10th sternite (ventral view); I̅K, phallic organs (ventral, ventrolateral, and lateral view, respectively); L, M, apical portion of paramere(s), gonopods, and aedeagus (caudal and lateral view, respectively); N, O, oviscapt (ventral and lateral view, respectively); P, spermatheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1439539/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="56">Fig. 9A,B</figureCitation>
): Apical seta present only on mid-tibia. Midleg 1 
<taxonomicName box="[1031,1172,260,284]" pageId="19" pageNumber="56" rank="subSpecies" subSpecies="tarsomere">st tarsomere</taxonomicName>
subproximally without spine.
</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1439539/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="56" startId="19.[151,250,1810,1832]" targetBox="[150,1436,373,1789]" targetPageId="19">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1436,1809,2016]" pageId="19" pageNumber="56">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,1405,1809,1832]" pageId="19" pageNumber="56">
FIGURE 9. 
<taxonomicName authority="Katoh &amp; Zhang &amp; Toda &amp; Zhang &amp; Gao, 2018" authorityName="Katoh &amp; Zhang &amp; Toda &amp; Zhang &amp; Gao" authorityYear="2018" box="[281,528,1810,1832]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Lordiphosa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="anthophilia" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[281,528,1810,1832]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="56">Lordiphosa anthophilia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[534,615,1810,1831]" pageId="19" pageNumber="56" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(A, B: paratype #05609; C −M: holotype #05610; N −P: paratype #05606).
</emphasis>
A, sex-combs on right foreleg (ventrolateral view); B, clusters of sex-comb teeth on distal extensions of 1 
<taxonomicName box="[1208,1272,1841,1863]" pageId="19" pageNumber="56" rank="subSpecies" subSpecies="and">st and</taxonomicName>
2nd tarsomeres (ventral view); C, D, periphallic organs (caudal and caudolateral view, respectively); E, epandrial ventral lobe (lateral view); F, surstyli and ventral spines of cercus (caudal view); G, inner surface of surstylus (caudolateral view); H, 10th sternite (ventral view); I̅K, phallic organs (ventral, ventrolateral, and lateral view, respectively); L, M, apical portion of paramere(s), gonopods, and aedeagus (caudal and lateral view, respectively); N, O, oviscapt (ventral and lateral view, respectively); P, spermatheca.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1437,151,1256]" pageId="20" pageNumber="57">Abdomen (Pl. 1E): Tergites nearly entirely black, sometimes anteriorly yellow to yellowish brown, somewhat glossy; tergite II entirely and III anterolaterally yellow to yellowish brown; female tergite VII yellow.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1437,151,1256]" pageId="20" pageNumber="57">
Male terminalia (
<figureCitation box="[414,554,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="19.[151,250,1810,1832]" captionTargetBox="[150,1436,373,1789]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[150,1436,373,1789]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 9. Lordiphosa anthophilia sp. nov. (A, B: paratype 05609; C−M: holotype 05610; N−P: paratype 05606). A, sex-combs on right foreleg (ventrolateral view); B, clusters of sex-comb teeth on distal extensions of 1st and 2nd tarsomeres (ventral view); C, D, periphallic organs (caudal and caudolateral view, respectively); E, epandrial ventral lobe (lateral view); F, surstyli and ventral spines of cercus (caudal view); G, inner surface of surstylus (caudolateral view); H, 10th sternite (ventral view); I̅K, phallic organs (ventral, ventrolateral, and lateral view, respectively); L, M, apical portion of paramere(s), gonopods, and aedeagus (caudal and lateral view, respectively); N, O, oviscapt (ventral and lateral view, respectively); P, spermatheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1439539/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="57">Fig. 9C–M</figureCitation>
): Epandrium yellowish brown, nearly entirely pubescent, caudodorsally triangularly notched, with ca. 24 long setae per side. Cercus yellowish brown, with ca. 19 long setae. Surstylus with a row of 15–16 prensisetae on caudal margin and 36–44 recurved setae on ventral portion of inner surface. Tenth sternite pale brown, moderately sclerotized, flat, medially not concaved. Gonopods rectangular in lateral view, dorsoapically without process, but dorsoproximally with small, claw-like projection. Aedeagus basally membranous, submedially to basally sheathed with gonopods.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1437,151,1256]" pageId="20" pageNumber="57">
Female terminalia (
<figureCitation box="[433,566,439,464]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="19.[151,250,1810,1832]" captionTargetBox="[150,1436,373,1789]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[150,1436,373,1789]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 9. Lordiphosa anthophilia sp. nov. (A, B: paratype 05609; C−M: holotype 05610; N−P: paratype 05606). A, sex-combs on right foreleg (ventrolateral view); B, clusters of sex-comb teeth on distal extensions of 1st and 2nd tarsomeres (ventral view); C, D, periphallic organs (caudal and caudolateral view, respectively); E, epandrial ventral lobe (lateral view); F, surstyli and ventral spines of cercus (caudal view); G, inner surface of surstylus (caudolateral view); H, 10th sternite (ventral view); I̅K, phallic organs (ventral, ventrolateral, and lateral view, respectively); L, M, apical portion of paramere(s), gonopods, and aedeagus (caudal and lateral view, respectively); N, O, oviscapt (ventral and lateral view, respectively); P, spermatheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1439539/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="57">Fig. 9N–O</figureCitation>
): Tergite VIII yellowish brown. Epiproct and hypoproct grayish brown. Oviscapt valve apicodorsally concave in lateral view, apically with 9̄10 and 8̄9 ovisensilla on dorsal and ventral margins, respectively, laterally with ca. 76 minute ovisensilla. Spermathecal capsule slightly broader than long; introvert about 3/4 height of capsule.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1437,151,1256]" pageId="20" pageNumber="57">
Measurements (in mm): BL = 
<quantity box="[542,621,583,608]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.1882" pageId="20" pageNumber="57" unit="in" value="2.83">2.83 in</quantity>
<typeStatus box="[628,726,583,608]" pageId="20" pageNumber="57">holotype</typeStatus>
(range in 
<specimenCount box="[841,879,583,608]" pageId="20" pageNumber="57" type="male">7♂</specimenCount>
/ 
<specimenCount box="[889,919,583,608]" pageId="20" pageNumber="57" type="female">5♀</specimenCount>
<typeStatus box="[927,1039,584,608]" pageId="20" pageNumber="57">paratypes</typeStatus>
: 2.18̄2.66/2.35̄2.94), ThL = 1.16 (1.08̄1.16/1.10̄1.28), WL = 2.72 (2.53̄2.73/2.66̄3.03), WW = 1.10 (1.02̄1.12/1.13̄1.23).
</paragraph>
